<br>
the taunt button. what does it do?<br>
<br>
some think it adds a certain somewhat fixed amount of hate to the taunter from the mob. it would follow that the best way to taunt is &quot;spam the taunt button&quot;.<br>
<br>
nope<br>
<br>
my observation is the taunt button does a success check. when it succeeds it grants the warrior agro. when it fails it does nothing.<br>
<br>
why do we care?<br>
<br>
because it affects our strategy a lot.<br>
<br>
consider the complete heal spell.<br>
&lt;&lt;INC CH on TANK&gt;&gt;<br>
<br>
taunt ... taunt .. taunt ...<br>
<br>
ch lands ...<br>
<br>
cleric gets whomped. warrior spins around looking for cleric and after 5 frantic seconds finally gets a taunt off on the mob.<br>
<br>
what went wrong? the taunt button was waiting for refresh thats what.<br>
<br>
now had that taunt button been up when the heal landed the warrior could have IMMEDIATELY hit it as soon as the heal landed and most of the time the taunt will yank that agro right back.<br>
<br>
im talking about timing that heal. im saying you watch your hitpoint bar and have the sound on and as soon as you hear and see that heal you whack that taunt button. you have about half a second to do it .. so be quick.<br>
<br>
wont always work. taunt has a check and when the check fails so do you.<br>
<br>
but it will work much more often than spamming the taunt button.<br>
<br>
multiple mobs lose taunt. what do you do?<br>
<br>
hit taunt ONCE and see if that mob is pulled back to you. immediately taunt the next mob ONCE. its not necessary to whack it for 5 seconds after the taunt. if the cleric doesnt cast another heal before you get the taunt back on all the mobs (and he probably wont hes getting hit) then only one taunt (that passes the check) is necessary.<br>
<br>
breaking mezzes ...<br>
<br>
the privelege of MT.<br>
<br>
taunt it first. taunt doesnt break mez. did you know that? then when you break mez you dont have to spin around trying to find it again.<br>
<br>
taunt doesnt pass its check always. but its much better than i used to realize.<br>
<br>
or maybe im full of it. im just a player still learning. if someone disagrees on some of these points im interested in hearing the real story about taunts. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=brittykilminster>Britty Kilminster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/26/03 6:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3218.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.optushome.com.au/arthurgiaa/Smurf.jpg width=95 height=128></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   *NT*</span><hr size=1> *no text*<br>
