<br>
There has been <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>extensive</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> testing on the workings of the taunt skill, and conclusive evidence has shown that taunting when you are already on top of the hate list either provides <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>no benefit</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> or the increase in hate is so miniscule as to be negligable. When the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.thesteelwarrior.org">new boards</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> are back up, dedicate a couple days to the taunt thread in the library.<br>
<br>
Mashing the taunt button constantly only provides for unreliable agro. If you've just wasted a taunt and your healer/slower/whatever takes agro, it's going to be another 6 seconds before you can even try to taunt again. If you're a taunt masher, try paying close attention to agro and timing your taunts to when you actually lose agro. I think you'll notice a difference. I am a reformed masher myself. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
